        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Is this something I can work on (if this is still something you want)? I did a little spelunking and [this](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/e62dd13f83a200105a2b8466e729c39485fa766d/runtime/syntax/doxygen.vim#L419) seems to be where the font is set. I could be wrong here, but it appears neovide ships with FiraCode NF ([source](https://github.com/neovide/neovide/blob/main/src/renderer/fonts/font_loader.rs#L19)), but I assume we don't want to do that, so maybe we choose a mono font that's reasonable and guaranteed to exist. [This MS page](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/fonts/windows_11_font_list) seems to indicate Cascadia Mono might be one of the few shipped with Windows 11, for example.\n\nAm I on the right track?",
