        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> it appears neovide ships with FiraCode NF ([source](https://github.com/neovide/neovide/blob/main/src/renderer/fonts/font_loader.rs#L19)), but I assume we don't want to do that,\n\nGUIs likely would choose their own defaults, no need for core to do that.\n\nThe task here is probably just to update `options.lua` here: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/e62dd13f83a200105a2b8466e729c39485fa766d/src/nvim/options.lua#L4009\n\nLook at how other options choose platform-specific defaults. Example: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/e62dd13f83a200105a2b8466e729c39485fa766d/src/nvim/options.lua#L7618-L7624\n\nThe main task here is just to find out which defaults are reasonable for each system.",
